article.description: Nicky Wieben scored 18 points to lead Iowa State to a 53-47 victory over Colorado on Saturday for the Cyclones' fifth straight win.
article.headline: Wieben's 18 points pave way for Iowa State's 5th straight win
article.linkText: Wieben leads way as Iowa St. edges Colorado
article.story:
BOULDER, Colo. -- Nicky Wieben scored 18 points to lead Iowa State (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP)
 to a 53-47 victory over Colorado on Saturday for the Cyclones' fifth straight win.

Iowa State (18-4, 6-2 Big 12) led by as many as 18 in the first half and went into halftime with a 31-22 lead. Colorado (10-11, 2-7) cut the deficit to five early in the second half but could get no closer.

Brittany Spears had 14 points and 12 rebounds for Colorado.

Iowa State has now held its last five opponents to 50 points or less.
